%p Haw Par Villa is a former amusement park that is now free for the public to visit. It displays a number of Chinese tales about good and evil with puppets. Part of the park is a tunnel with the 10 stages of hell a bad person has to go through.

.photo-row
  %img{:src => '//cdn.matsimitsu.com/asia2015/day-four/image-1-1100x.jpg', :width => '1100', :height => '730'}
  %img{:src => '//cdn.matsimitsu.com/asia2015/day-four/image-2-1100x.jpg', :width => '1100', :height => '730'}

%p The characters are totally random and vary between rabbits, people and bears.

.photo-row
  %img{:src => '//cdn.matsimitsu.com/asia2015/day-four/image-3-1100x.jpg', :width => '1100', :height => '730'}
  %img{:src => '//cdn.matsimitsu.com/asia2015/day-four/image-4-1100x.jpg', :width => '1100', :height => '730'}

