.photo-row
  %img{:src => '//cdn.matsimitsu.com/asia2015/day-four/image-13-1100x.jpg', :width => '1100', :height => '733'}
  %img{:src => '//cdn.matsimitsu.com/asia2015/day-four/image-14-1100x.jpg', :width => '1100', :height => '733'}

%p Fortunately they started restoring the park by re-painting all the displays.

%img{:src => '//cdn.matsimitsu.com/asia2015/day-four/image-15-1100x.jpg', :width => '1100', :height => '733'}

%p After the park we headed back to the subway to go to Sentosa Island.
%img{:src => '//cdn.matsimitsu.com/asia2015/day-four/image-16-1100x.jpg', :width => '1100', :height => '733'}

%p This the entertainment island with Universal studios, beaches, water parks and pretty much every other form of entertainment you can imagine.

.photo-row
  %img{:src => '//cdn.matsimitsu.com/asia2015/day-four/image-6-1100x.jpg', :width => '1100', :height => '730'}
  %img{:src => '//cdn.matsimitsu.com/asia2015/day-four/image-17-1100x.jpg', :width => '1100', :height => '733'}

%p We settled with just visiting the beach. In the background you can see hundreds of ships anchored, waiting for a job. On the other side of the cable car is Mount Faber. It offers a nice view of the city.

.photo-row
  %img{:src => '//cdn.matsimitsu.com/asia2015/day-four/image-18-1100x.jpg', :width => '1100', :height => '733'}
  %img{:src => '//cdn.matsimitsu.com/asia2015/day-four/image-19-1100x.jpg', :width => '1100', :height => '733'}

%p The evening was setting in, it was time for our final evening in Singapore. We headed to the Gardens at the Bay, a giant park near the waterfront. One of the attractions is an indoor "Cloud walk" where you walk down a giant mountain covered with plants.

%img{:src => '//cdn.matsimitsu.com/asia2015/day-four/image-7-1100x.jpg', :width => '1100', :height => '730'}

.photo-row
  %img{:src => '//cdn.matsimitsu.com/asia2015/day-four/image-20-1100x.jpg', :width => '1100', :height => '733'}
  %img{:src => '//cdn.matsimitsu.com/asia2015/day-four/image-8-1100x.jpg', :width => '1100', :height => '730'}

%p Outside are the most know features of the park, Giant towers covered in plants and emitting lights. You can take a skywalk between the towers, but we got there too late to buy tickets. Fortunatley a nice man approached us and gave his tickets so we were the last to take the walk that day.

